snippet.textDisplay: Grew up on a farm in MT.  Had a dairy cow who gave 5 gallons per day at peak.  We made A LOT of cheese.  Mom's most notable one was a jalapeno cheddar that came with slices of the peppers in the cheese.  Moz was always my favorite to make because when it was fresh mom would spread it over her double decker pizza (Think giant calzone that filled a cookie sheet and weighed 9 lbs when it went in the oven).  Ethan, the reason the moz got crumbly is probably because you let it get too hot or didn't remove the whey well enough.
snippet.textOriginal: Grew up on a farm in MT.  Had a dairy cow who gave 5 gallons per day at peak.  We made A LOT of cheese.  Mom's most notable one was a jalapeno cheddar that came with slices of the peppers in the cheese.  Moz was always my favorite to make because when it was fresh mom would spread it over her double decker pizza (Think giant calzone that filled a cookie sheet and weighed 9 lbs when it went in the oven).
